A MongoDB cluster is a group of interconnected servers (nodes) that work together to store data,
providing high availability, redundancy, and horizontal scaling

“MongoDB cluster ka matlab hota hai multiple servers ka group
jo ek saath database ko manage karte hain. Isse system highly available rehta hai,
data multiple nodes par safe rehta hai, aur load badhne par easily new
servers add karke scale kiya ja sakta hai.”

👉 Mongoose is an Object Data Modeling (ODM) library for Node.js that provides a structured way to
interact with MongoDB by defining schemas, enforcing validation, and simplifying database operations.

👉 “Mongoose is an ODM library that helps structure and manage MongoDB data in Node.js.”